metadata.name: Slumbers #299
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: System α #261
metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"α" means the first step of this series.

Press [s] in live view to save file as PNG.
Press [p] to stop.

metadata.name: Kinetograms #265
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #172
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Artifice #223
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Mei(梅) #2
metadata.description:
Mei(梅):

"Mei" is an oriental art piece featuring the imagery of plum blossom, a symbol of courage and perseverance in traditional Chinese culture.

The generative system at the backend of "Mei" is an exploration of this cultural symbol by modern art language. The basic elements of the paintings are merely circles and enclosed flow field shapes. A great variety of short and light strokes of such elements are used across the paintings. Xuan paper is occasionally used as background, which is a painting material since the Tang dynasty.

Mei's outputs span different stages of plum blossom from winter to spring. The scene also changes from a calm day to snowy or even stormy weather. The consistent yet complex senses and feelings reflected are surprisingly versatile.

metadata.name: Punktwelt #217
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: the boxes we live in #408
metadata.description:
Throughout our lives we are placed in boxes that define who we are and limit how we think of ourselves. 

I am a father, husband, son, brother, friend. I am an artist, programmer, photographer, musician, designer, creator. I am a student and I am a teacher. I am a good person. I am a bad person. I am a human.

What boxes do you put yourself in, and do you let others put you in? Is it possible to break out of the boxes that define your life? Do you even want to? What's outside of these boundaries? What is at the center?

metadata.name: Pot #26
metadata.description:
Pots are a series of generative painted vases archived on the ipfs as an artifact of the digital age.

54 fxrand() calls and 4 different noise algorithms bend and paint the geometry.

Users can download the generated sculpture and texture as a .glb

The code is uncompressed for anybody interested.

metadata.name: PIPES #14
metadata.description:
PIPES are its own creatures growing out of an Octree, swirling and twirling towards each's individual destination.  

Features:   
  There are four different flow modes, seven different palettes.   
  PIPES can either be hollow or filled, and there is a small chance the PIPES is drawn in gradient.  

Loading time is about 6s and then it will start to animate. Thank you for your patience.  

Press 'S' to save a high resolution 4800x4800px PNG of the artwork.  

This work is made purely with p5js.

metadata.name: Balancium #811
metadata.description:
"Balancium" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

In the fall of 1931, in Alexander Calder's studio, Marcel Duchamp coined the term 'mobile' for his kinetic sculptures. Later, Calder wrote: "This, in French, means not only 'movable'— but also a 'motive', 'a reason for an act' so I found it a very good word."
 
Around the same year, Bruno Munari started making colorful and whimsical mobiles. He called them "useless machines", existing without any purpose and inviting viewers to just look. Elements are connected with nearly invisible threads or wires, allowing the artist to create the illusion of shapes floating in the air.

Balancium is both a virtual mobile and a useless object. Generated by the code, it undergoes a continual transformation. The movement of the air, or invisible fluid, becomes an integral part of the design and amplifies serenity. 
 
There is a keyboard key that unlocks more variations.
